Todd wrote:

>>When I drive over 45 miles an hour, one of the wheels in the front, maybe
one, maybe both... starts wobbling like crazy. The steering wheel really
REALLY gives me the feedback too.. 
 
What specifically on the suspension could cause this problem?<<

first things that come to mind are:
-wheel bearings
-ball joints
-tie rods

put your bus up on jackstands & try to wiggle some of the suspension parts.
that might give you an idea of what is going on.

